3e2f48e3-c2e8-4e5e-9951-4e78e682a492.do_description: To make the output, you have to...count the number of colors in input, then according to the count, each grid size is changed within  each block. And each block should be colored as same in input

3e2f48e3-c2e8-4e5e-9951-4e78e682a492.see_description: In the input, you should see...3x3 colored pattern

6d0d39ee-acab-4cca-9334-53fa258331b9.do_description: To make the output, you have to...create either 2x2, 3x3, or 4x4 blocks of the original color in the input.

6d0d39ee-acab-4cca-9334-53fa258331b9.see_description: In the input, you should see...a series of colored blocks on a black background.

942216d8-413c-46cc-aa22-2cadea946fc2.do_description: To make the output, you have to...re-create the same pattern with a single pixel becoming a square with sides of length corresponding to the number of colors in the original pattern.  In other words, simply increase the resolution of the input  by the number of colors it contains.
942216d8-413c-46cc-aa22-2cadea946fc2.grid_description: The output grid size...is the number of colors in the pattern times 3 for both width and height
942216d8-413c-46cc-aa22-2cadea946fc2.see_description: In the input, you should see...a random pattern of pixels

fc0c0f00-3f5e-4115-9041-68ac5ea1b30b.do_description: To make the output, you have to... just multiply the size of the output grid as stated in the last sentence, but make sure the colors take up as much space as before (if it's a 9x9 grid, each color square will be 3x3, for instance).
